<br>
“I’m only going to say this once,” she said. “I’m not your Chloe and I don’t want anything to do with the person responsible for her death.” Her voice was shaky, but confident. Clark furrowed his brow.<br>
<br>
“What are you talking about sweetheart?” He asked in confusion. Then Clark noticed Lex and anger marred his features. “You’re not going back to him,” he growled and ripped her away from Lex’s embrace.<br>
<br>
“Ouch!” Chloe yelped. Now she was angry. She hit Clark’s chest hard, but pulled back her hand when she felt like she had broken every bone in it. “Damn it!” Clark pulled her closer so their bodies were flush against each other. She couldn’t help thinking that not long ago, in her reality; she would have loved to be in Clark’s arms. And now she was just struggling to get away from him.<br>
<br>
“Let her go!” Lex demanded. Clark didn’t even look at him; he kept his intense gaze on Chloe.<br>
<br>
“I love you Chloe.” Clark stroked her hair. “And you love me. Why are you trying to get away from me?” Chloe fumed.<br>
<br>
“I’m not your Chloe!” She repeated. “And the Clark Kent I know would have never ordered my death, let alone sleep with a married woman. Now let me go!” Clark was confused, but he figured that Lex had done something to her to make her forget the love they shared. He leaned down to kiss her. She turned her head to avoid his lips and he squared his jaw. Clark released her for a moment.<br>
<br>
