<br>
“Would he want you to stay there without him?” Lex asked, trying to get her to come to her senses. “Because that’s how it would be. You said Clark killed him, remember?” Chloe sniffled and looked up at Lex with wet eyes.<br>
<br>
“I,” she paused when she everything clicked for her. “I,” she repeated. “I’m sorry.” “I need to go home. Something happened to me and,” she shook her head slightly, “I think I need some rest.” Without asking, Lex placed his hand on the small of her back.<br>
<br>
“I’ll give you a ride,” he stated. She gave him an odd expression.<br>
<br>
“I don’t think that would be a very good idea,” Chloe rasped. Lex stood his ground and Chloe knew from the look on his face that he wasn’t going to let her leave with anyone else. She took in a deep breath and nodded once. “Okay.” Pete looked at her like she had gone crazy.<br>
<br>
